          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Approximate 1/E spectrum"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Pu-dioxide, isotopic purity of Pu-244 98.58%.",
                " two 12.5 micrometer thick stainless steel backings",
                " with deposits of 180 microgram/cm**2 Pu-O(2) were",
                " placed back-to-back into the fission chamber.",
                " diameter of deposit 10 cm. (Linac-TOF measurement)",
                ".Pu-dioxide,",
                " two 0.5 mm thick stainless steel backings with",
                " deposits of 150 microgram/cm**2 Pu-O(2) and",
                " 213 microgram/cm**2 235-U(3)-O(8) were placed",
                " back-to-back into the chamber.",
                " diameter of deposit 2.8 Cm (VDG measurement)",
                ".For the neutron flux measurement a 235-U(3)-O(8)",
                " sample was used, thickness 380 microgram/cm**2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " time-of-flight path of 25 meter.",
                ".As a cross check of the tof-data measured with the",
                " linac, two additional measurements at 2.0 and 2.5 MeV",
                " were carried out. The chamber was in zero degree",
                " direction to the beam, the distance neutron-source",
                " to sample was 8 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " parallel plate ionization chamber with",
                ".nano-sec timing.ref. Knitter and Budtz-Joergensen",
                " in (C,KNOX79)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The data are based on a normalization which is the",
                " weighted average of both measurements. The authors",
                " point out that the two measurements were essentially",
                " independent.",
                ".Calculation of the exact 'effective' Pu sample masses."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "92-U-235(N,F),,SIG",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "92-U-235(N,F),,SIG",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "92-U-235(N,F)",
                        "target": "92-U-235",
                        "projectile": "N",
                        "process": "F",
                        "product": "",
                        "quantity": ",SIG",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",SIG"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                ".Above 25 keV the ENDF/B-V data were assumed for",
                " the fission cross section.",
                ".Below 25 keV the assumed data are based on fission",
                " cross section integrals as measured by Wagemans and",
                " Deruytter (J,ANE,3,437,76)."
              ]
            }
          ],
